The paper proposes a method for causal discovery using reinforcement learning, which involves training an encoder-decoder model to generate graph adjacency matrices that are used to compute rewards. This approach falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is reflected in the likely sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.AI. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of discovering causal structure among a set of variables, which is a common problem in statistics and data mining, making sub-categories such as cs.SI and cs.DM likely as well. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to enforcing acyclicity in the generated graphs, which could be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science).
